&lt;p&gt;Service/Ward/Department Summary:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This service for young people and adults with suspected ASD and ADHD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer: Diagnosis and post-diagnostic support for ASD and ADHD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Team is multi-disciplinary and is based at Stepping Hill Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Role Summary:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be a member of the ADHD/ASD service. The post holder is responsible for providing assessment and formulation for adults presenting with ADHD/ASD and provide evidence based interventions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities of the Post:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure high quality assessment of young people and adults referred to the ADHD/ASD service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To work effectively within the MDT respecting all disciplines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To recognise and effectively manage acute risk and mental illness, ensuring good links and referral pathways to other service such as Access and Adult Social Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Requirements of the Person Specification:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RMN/RGN&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to safeguarding and promoting the welfare of children and vulnerable adults and expect all employees and volunteers to share this commitment. Appointments to regulated and controlled activities will require an enhanced CRB disclosure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameRebecca RaticanJob titleTeam ManagerEmail addressrebecca.ratican@nhs.netTelephone number0161 716 4591&lt;/p&gt;
